article.description: Kyle Havens threw for two first-half touchdowns, and Massachusetts defeated Rhode Island 30-10 on Saturday.
article.headline: Massachusetts' defense holds Rhode Island to 25 rushing yards
article.linkText: Massachusetts cruises to win over Rhode Island
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- Kyle Havens threw for two first-half touchdowns, and Massachusetts defeated Rhode Island 30-10 on Saturday. Havens, who averaged 11 yards a pass, was 22-of-30 for 329 yards. After scoring passes of 4 and 5 yards, and a 3-yard TD rush by Tony Nelson, the Minutemen (2-1) led 21-0 at halftime in the Colonial Athletic Association opener for both teams. Nelson rushed for 158 yards and a touchdown on 29 carries for Massachusetts. Victor Cruz added 96 yards and a touchdown on six catches for the Minutemen. Massachusetts had 491 total yards of offense and held Rhode Island to 25 rushing yards. Chris Paul-Etienne was 20-of-39 for 198 yards and an interception for the Rams (1-1).
